<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB01338</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT INCREASING THE SERVICE INCENTIVE LEAVE OF EMPLOYEES, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE ARTICLE 95 OF PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 442, AS AMENDED, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE LABOR CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Increasing The Service Incentive Leave Of Employees, Amending For The Purpose Article 95 Of Presidential Decree No. 442, As Amended, Otherwise Known As The Labor Code Of The Philippines</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims To Increase The Service Incentive Leave To Ten (10) Days With Pay Of Every Employee Who Has Rendered At Least One Year Of Service Except Those Enjoying Vacation Leave With Pay Of At Least Ten (10) Days And Those Employed In Establishments Regularly Employing Less Than Ten Employees Or In Establishments Exempted From Granting This Benefit By The Secretary Of Labor And Employment After Considering The Viability Or Financial Condition Of Such Establishment.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>GO, MARK O., VILLAFUERTE, LUIS RAYMUND &quot;LRAY&quot; JR F., MANGAOANG, ALLEN JESSE C., PINEDA, ENRICO A., AGLIPAY, MICHAEL EDGAR Y., MENDOZA, RAYMUND DEMOCRITO C., COLLANTES, MA. THERESA V., BABASA, LEONARDO JR. L., CABREDO, FERNANDO T., TADURAN, ROWENA NI&Ntilde;A O., DELOSO-MONTALLA, CHERYL P., FORTUN, LAWRENCE &quot;LAW&quot; H., GAITE, FERDINAND R., NOGRALES, JERICHO JONAS B., DALIPE, MANUEL JOSE &quot;MANNIX&quot; M., DAGOOC, SERGIO C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-03</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>AUTHORS(Committee Report) :</td></tr><tr><td width='%33'>1. Go (M.)</td><td width='33%'>2. Villafuerte</td><td width='34%'>3. Mangaoang</td></tr><tr><td width='%33'>4. Pineda</td><td width='33%'>5. Aglipay</td><td width='34%'>6. Mendoza</td></tr><tr><td width='%33'>7. Collantes</td><